From f35a50e3d7abe529df8ab75a8a31207b4e02cbfb Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: LIU Hao <lh_mouse@126.com>
Date: Tue, 30 Jun 2026 10:17:12 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 9205/9205] libgomp/win32: Add win32 implementation

This commit adds a set of headers and source files for *-*-mingw* which use
Windows APIs directly, so libgomp can built for said targets when not using
the posix thread model.

libgomp/ChangeLog:

	* affinity-fmt.c (gomp_display_affinity): Enable for `_WIN32`.
	* config/posix/bar.h: Remove unused include <pthread.h>.
	* configure: Regenerate.
	* configure.ac: Check for thread model for *-*-mingw*.
	* configure.tgt: Include config/win32 for non-posix for *-*-mingw*.
	* env.c (initialize_env): Skip pthread functions when not using
	pthreads.  Set `gomp_win32_thread_stack_size` for non-posix thread
	models for Windows.
	* libgomp.h: Un-include <pthread.h> when not using pthreads.
	(GOMP_NEEDS_THREAD_HANDLE): Define for non-posix thread models for
	*-*-mingw*.  But we actually use the numeric thread ID.
	(__mingwthr_key_dtor): Declare for internal use.
	(__mingwthr_remove_key_dtor): Declare for internal use.
	(gomp_thread_self): Implement for win32 non-posix.
	(gomp_thread_to_pthread_t): Implement for win32 non-posix.
	* oacc-init.c (acc_init_thread): Undefine when not using pthreads.
	(acc_init_win32_thread_id): Define for win32 non-posix.
	* target.c (gomp_is_initialized): Undefine when not using pthreads.
	(gomp_win32_once): Define for win32 non-posix.
	* task.c (gomp_create_artificial_team): Do not call
	`pthread_setspecific()` when not using pthreads.  Call `TlsSetValue()`
	for win32 non-posix.
	* team.c: Include <float.h> for mingw-w64.
	(gomp_thread_attr): Undefine when not using pthreads.
	(gomp_thread_destructor): Likewise.
	(gomp_win32_thread_stack_size): Define for win32 non-posix.
	(gomp_win32_tls_index): Likewise.
	(gomp_thread_start_data): Do not store `pthread_t` when not using
	pthreads.  Add thread ID field for win32 non-posix.
	(gomp_thread_start): Change calling convention for win32 non-posix.
	Call `_fpreset()` to initialize x87 precision for all thread models
	for *-*-mingw*.  Skip pthread functions when not using pthreads.
	Set `win32_thread_id` for win32 non-posix.
	(gomp_team_start): Skip pthread functions when not using pthreads.
	Add win32 non-posix implementation.
	(gomp_pause_host): Likewise.
	(gomp_free_pool_helper): Likewise.
	(gomp_pause_pool_helper): Likewise.
	* config/win32/lock.c: New file.
	* config/win32/mutex.c: New file.
	* config/win32/mutex.h: New file.
	* config/win32/omp-lock.h: New file.
	* config/win32/pool.h: New file.
	* config/win32/sem.c: New file.
	* config/win32/sem.h: New file.

Signed-off-by: LIU Hao <lh_mouse@126.com>
